(and revised, and will make further changes too as nesscary).<br>
a new looting system for our raids, effective as of this posting.<br>
<br>
Loot will be handled on a more senority basis, then todays total random, we realized alot of our raiders were repeat raiders, having been there for multiple raids for chances at an item. So heres how it works.<br>
<br>
You make your intentions clear as to specifically what item it is you want.<br>
For every raid you attend, you earn a Raid-Point.<br>
If the item you declared itentions for drops, and you lead the charts by a margin of 2 points you will be awarded the item without rolling, and your raid-points reset to 0.<br>
(example: you want a torbin's eyepatch, you have 9 raidpoints, and next highest person who wanted the eyepatch has 7, if one drops, you are awarded the item without a roll, and reset to 0)<br>
If there is a margin of only one (you have nine and other person has 8, going with above example) or there are equal numbers, you will be requires to random for the item with your peer. Winner being reset to 0.<br>
<br>
53+ lvl helpers ALSO earn raidpoints, but....it must be exceptionally clear that your presence made a difference, simply being there with the intention of helping is not enough.<br>
(example: your a 55 cleric you come to raid to help, but i have already done the rounds and cleric buffed all groups, etc, you do not earn a raidpoint or chance at loot, well this may not seem fair, the situation of a leech has already arised once and this is only way to deal with it.)<br>
Examples of helping:<br>
Buffing players when told to by one of the raid-masters.<br>
Explaining in detail tactics, answering questions to those less knowledgeable<br>
Clearing the fire or ice giants *IF* you were needed for it (example: you, me, and 2 others are very early, and start clearing the giants, not..we organize 30 people..THEN start clearing the giants, and you just jump in)<br>
<br>
To qualify for certain loot you must have a minimum of raidpoints, currently only the scales and paladin books have this requirement and it is a meager 2 points.<br>
In the case of scales, they will be awarded only for epics at first unless absolutley no one needs them on our roster anymore. And those further along in thier epic, may be given preferance on scales (Undecided fully as yet.)<br>
<br>
Certain other loot will be designated as &quot;everyone&quot;  and &quot;double&quot; items such as a golden plated kosignata and dragonbone bracer.<br>
&quot;Everyone&quot; items may be rolled on by any class that had no loot for them drop on that particular raid.<br>
&quot;Double&quot; items as same as everyone items, but only when TWO drop, and the second one only. the first one follows normal looting rules.<br>
<br>
And last, a few ground-raid rules in general.<br>
<br>
First, and this is very important and strictly enforced.<br>
NO ONE, except a designated raid-master is allowed to loot a  dragon corpse. If *anyone* besides one is seen bending over a corpse, you will be immedatley be /reported, and /petitioned regardless of wether or not you stole any item, and will not be invited back. This may seem harsh, but is unfortunetly nesscary when dealing with alot of unknown people, who could be of dubious personality.<br>
<br>
Second, the loot you earn at our raids *IS NOT* for sale, if you are found to be selling it, you will not be invited back, and will earn earn a public whip lashing! =0 j/k<br>
The only exception to this rule is everyone/double items, if you cannot use the item, you are free to sell/trade it.<br>
<br>
Third, Whining or resentment over loot will not be tolerated to a degree, if you do not like our rules, we dont force you to attend, its simple as that, and any over-whiners, will not be invited back.<br>
<br>
I look forward to working with all of you in the future =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukadorthechampion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kador the champion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regular Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/30/01 5:40:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> loot rules</span><hr size=1> I started tallying who was at the nagafen raid last night and the points will be carried over to the vox raid today.<br>
